---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Made by Multitudes" page="about">
  <article class="shell shell--narrow" style="padding: 0;">
    <header style="margin-bottom: 3.5rem;">
      <p class="mono" style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">About</p>
      <h1 style="max-width: 14ch;">
        I am large, I contain multitudes.
      </h1>
      <p class="mono-line" style="margin-top: 0.8rem;">— Walt Whitman, by way of borrowed permission</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Made by Multitudes is a small studio and a holding company for a few
        related practices. The work splits roughly into product design,
        service design, and the occasional advisory engagement. The name is a
        confession that one person, even one studio, contains more than one
        kind of work — and that the things we ship are made by many hands,
        even when only one is paid.
      </p>

      <p>
        We started in 2021 with a single client and a domain name. Today we
        run as a deliberately small operation — small enough to know every
        project intimately, large enough to take on more than one at a time.
        We do not have a stack of case studies for you to scroll. We have a
        list of names, a few writings, and a working email address.
      </p>

      <h2>What the studio does</h2>

      <p>
        Mostly: we help teams figure out the shape of a thing before they
        spend a year building it. Sometimes that's a product. More often,
        once you look closely, it's a service — a set of human and software
        steps strung together, with the software bits getting most of the
        attention and the human bits getting most of the friction. We are
        interested in the human bits.
      </p>

      <p>
        We work best with founders and small teams in the first eighteen
        months of an idea. We also do longer engagements with operating
        companies who want a designer in the room when decisions get made,
        not after.
      </p>

      <h2>How we work</h2>

      <blockquote>
        Work that takes longer to make tends to last longer. We try to
        operate accordingly.
      </blockquote>

      <p>
        Engagements run in monthly cycles. We bill by the month, not the
        deliverable. We share work in progress weekly. We do not produce
        decks unless someone needs one to convince someone else, in which
        case we produce a good one.
      </p>

      <h2>Who is behind this</h2>

      <p>
        The studio is led by Matt Smith. Specific projects are made
        alongside a rotating set of collaborators — engineers, writers,
        researchers, illustrators — most of whom run their own small
        practices. The multitudes in the name are real.
      </p>

      <dl class="about-grid">
        <dt>Founded</dt>
        <dd>2021</dd>

        <dt>Practice</dt>
        <dd>Product &amp; service design, advisory</dd>

        <dt>Location</dt>
        <dd>Distributed</dd>

        <dt>Availability</dt>
        <dd>Booking from Q3</dd>

        <dt>Contact</dt>
        <dd>
          <a href="mailto:hello@madebymultitudes.com">hello@madebymultitudes.com</a>
        </dd>

        <dt>Elsewhere</dt>
        <dd>
          <a href="https://thisismattsmith.com">thisismattsmith.com</a>,
          <a href="https://github.com/thisismattsmith/">GitHub</a>,
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thisismattsmith/">LinkedIn</a>
        </dd>
      </dl>

      <p class="mono-line" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
        Last updated · {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { month: 'long', year: 'numeric' })}
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
